article.headline: Tulsa 74, TCU 66
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Jordan Clarkson scored 23 points and Kodi Maduka added 15 points and 15 rebounds to lead Tulsa to a 74-66 victory against TCU on Saturday night. Scottie Haralson and Eric McClellan had nine points each for the Golden Hurricane (7-7), who won for the 10th time in the last 11 meetings between the schools, dating to the 1998-99 season. Hank Thorns scored 16 points and Craig Williams and Garlon Green added 11 each for the Horned Frogs (8-5). The Hurricane scored a game's last eight points. Clarkson's jumper with 1:34 to play gave Tulsa a 68-66 lead, and TCU got just one shot on its final four possessions, missing all of them. With the Horned Frogs forced to foul, Maduka hit two free throws and Clarkson four down the stretch. Tulsa shot 50 percent (20 of 40) from the floor to TCU's 36.7 percent (18 of 49) and enjoyed a 35-27 rebounding advantage.
